headline: PLDT (PSE:TEL) Reports Q2 Revenue Growth; Considers Cash Dividend
summary: PLDT (PSE:TEL) recently held a board meeting to discuss its financial results and possible cash dividends, coinciding with the release of its notable second-quarter financial performance that showed revenue and net income growth, although net income was down over six months. Over the past month, PLDT's stock rose by 7%, aligning with broader market optimism reflected by the S&P 500 and Nasdaq reaching all-time highs. headline: Marine Sensors Market to Reach $1.9 Billion by 2028, Growing at 6.5% CAGR: Exploring the Depths of Growth
summary: Delray Beach, FL, Aug. 11, 2025 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- The Marine Sensors Market size was estimated at USD 1.3 billion in 2022 and is predicted to increase from USD 1.4 Billion in 2023 to approximately USD 1.9 Billion by 2028, expanding at a CAGR of 6.5% from 2023 to 2028. The Marine Sensors Industry is driven by factors such as increasing demand for UUV’s and AUV’, along with the increasing demand of the maritime transportation, navies are focusing on technologically advanced marine vessels.
